text: Been messing with my friend's Licia deck for a few weeks, and I think we've just come to the conclusion that he's better off running Kresh.

He's had a tough time making there be other threats in the deck besides Licia that work in a synergistic way. Kresh solves that so easily. The Doubling Season you'd be running for Kresh also is gross with Kalonian Hydra, etc. plus if you kill the hydra it buffs Kresh. The non-commander threats work with the commander, and they work with the stuff that works with the commander
Seems like a completely different deck with the only comparison being they're aggressive.
it's a rough build around that is for sure
the red in her makes for some interesting possibilities in terms of turning life gain into a weapon
but most of the ones that I am thinking of hurt you too
that being said, [[rain of gore]] doesn't stop lifelink
